TY  - JOUR
T1  - Gainsharing And Mutual Monitoring: A Combined Agency-Organizational Justice Interpretation
AU  - Welbourne, Theresa M.
AU  - Balkin, David B.
AU  - Gomez-Mejia, Luis R.
Y1  - 1995/06/01
PY  - 1995
DA  - 1995/06/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/256750
DO  - 10.5465/256750
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 881
EP  - 899
VL  - 38
IS  - 3
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - This study examines the behavioral consequences of ?gainsharing? using a theoretical framework that includes elements of agency and organizational justice theory. We propose that when gainsharing is used as a collective form of incentive alignment, mutual monitoring among employees is a direct function of procedural and distributive fairness. The hypothesis was supported in a quasi-experimental field study of 221 employees working for two firms. The implications of the study for future extensions of agency theory to intraorganizational phenomena are discussed.
AB  - This study examines the behavioral consequences of ?gainsharing? using a theoretical framework that includes elements of agency and organizational justice theory. We propose that when gainsharing is used as a collective form of incentive alignment, mutual monitoring among employees is a direct function of procedural and distributive fairness. The hypothesis was supported in a quasi-experimental field study of 221 employees working for two firms. The implications of the study for future extensions of agency theory to intraorganizational phenomena are discussed.
SN  - 0001-4273
M3  - doi: 10.5465/256750
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/256750
Y2  - 2026/04/24
