TY  - JOUR
T1  - Organizational Restructuring And Economic Performance In Leveraged Buyouts: An Ex Post Study
AU  - Phan, Phillip H.
AU  - Hill, Charles W. L.
Y1  - 1995/06/01
PY  - 1995
DA  - 1995/06/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/256743
DO  - 10.5465/256743
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 704
EP  - 739
VL  - 38
IS  - 3
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - This article reports the results of an ex post study of the effects of leveraged buyouts (LBOs) upon the goals, strategy, structure, and performance of firms. Our study was designed to test arguments that can be logically derived from agency theory. We used a survey to collect data on pre- and post LBO goals, strategy, structure, and productivity for a sample of 214 firms that underwent buyouts between 1986 and 1989. Our results do not enable us to reject hypotheses based upon agency theory.
AB  - This article reports the results of an ex post study of the effects of leveraged buyouts (LBOs) upon the goals, strategy, structure, and performance of firms. Our study was designed to test arguments that can be logically derived from agency theory. We used a survey to collect data on pre- and post LBO goals, strategy, structure, and productivity for a sample of 214 firms that underwent buyouts between 1986 and 1989. Our results do not enable us to reject hypotheses based upon agency theory.
SN  - 0001-4273
M3  - doi: 10.5465/256743
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/256743
