T1  - Predicting The Outcome Of A Contract Ratification Vote
AU  - Martin, James E.
AU  - Berthiaume, Ruth D.
Y1  - 1995/06/01
PY  - 1995
DA  - 1995/06/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/256752
DO  - 10.5465/256752
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 916
EP  - 928
VL  - 38
IS  - 3
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - This study examined the role of employee assessments of psychological and material factors in predicting the outcome of a contract ratification vote. The results show that both the material aspects of the contract settlement at hand and how members feel about their union and their jobs have an important impact on the ratification outcome.
AB  - This study examined the role of employee assessments of psychological and material factors in predicting the outcome of a contract ratification vote. The results show that both the material aspects of the contract settlement at hand and how members feel about their union and their jobs have an important impact on the ratification outcome.
