TY  - JOUR
T1  - Shareholder Value Creation During R&D Innovation And Commercialization Stages
AU  - Kelm, Kathryn M.
AU  - Narayanan, V. K.
AU  - Pinches, George E.
Y1  - 1995/06/01
PY  - 1995
DA  - 1995/06/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/256745
DO  - 10.5465/256745
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 770
EP  - 786
VL  - 38
IS  - 3
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - We examined the impact on the market value of firms' stock of announcements about R&D projects made in the innovation and commercialization stages of the R&D process. Technology- and market-related variables were tested as predictors of the wealth impact of R&D announcements. Our analysis indicates that the stage of the R&D process moderates the relationship between the wealth effects and technology and market variables. The former are more important than market variables in the innovation stage, and both are important during commercialization.
AB  - We examined the impact on the market value of firms' stock of announcements about R&D projects made in the innovation and commercialization stages of the R&D process. Technology- and market-related variables were tested as predictors of the wealth impact of R&D announcements. Our analysis indicates that the stage of the R&D process moderates the relationship between the wealth effects and technology and market variables. The former are more important than market variables in the innovation stage, and both are important during commercialization.
SN  - 0001-4273
M3  - doi: 10.5465/256745
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/256745
Y2  - 2026/04/24
